cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for automated cell tracking in microscopy sequences. This involves cell proposal generation and selection using a graphical model. The method is evaluated on multiple microscopy sequences and outperforms existing cell tracking methods. Given the focus on computer vision and machine learning techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep learning also suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The use of microscopy data and biological processes suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of a graphical model and joint cell detection and tracking suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible sub-category.
